SIMPLE: mankind
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mankind
<hw>man`kind"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>mancynn</ets>. See <er>Kin</er> kindred, <er>Kind</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The human race; man, taken
collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The proper study of <qex>mankind</qex> is man.</q>
<rj><qau>Pore.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Men, as distinguished from women; the male portion
of human race.</def> <rj><au>Lev. xviii. 22.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Human feelings; humanity.</def> <mark>[Obs]</mark>
<rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mankind</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mankind
<hw>Man"kind`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Manlike; not
womanly; masculine; bold; cruel.</def> <mark>[Obs]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Are women grown so <qex>mankind</qex>? Must they be wooing?</q>
<rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Be not too <qex>mankind</qex> against your wife.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manks</ent>⟦br⟧
